⸻

Core Pattern (One-Breath Rule)

Direction → Feedback → Alignment → Iterate

⸻

Expanded (still minimal)

Belief sets direction. Reality gives feedback. Conscience governs action. Repeat until stable.

⸻

Operational Loop (runnable)

1. Set Direction → What am I aiming at?
2. Act → Take a step
3. Observe → What actually happened?
4. Check Alignment → Was that right / true / useful?
5. Adjust → Correct course
6. Repeat

⸻

Invariants (must stay true)

* No direction → drift
* No feedback → delusion
* No conscience → misalignment
* No iteration → stagnation

⸻

Failure Tests

* Can this be applied in a new domain? (business, relationships, learning)
* Does it still work if reworded?
* Can someone use it in under 60 seconds?

If yes → it survives.

